Uses of Package
js

Packages that use js
js Opaque classes and interfaces necessary to simulate JavaScript features, and internal classes for simulative implementation. 
js.core Opaque classes simulating core JavaScript objects. 
js.dom Opaque classes and interfaces simulating client-side DOM. 
js.user Opaque classes simulating client-side JavaScript objects. 
jsx Fundamental JS Extension classes. 
jsx.client Utility classes handling JavaScript client objects. 
jsx.core Utility classes handling JavaScript core objects. 
jsx.dom Utility classes handling JavaScript DOM objects. 
jsx.dom.query Provides an efficient DOM querying mechanism. 
jsx.event Deals with browser-level events eliminating dependencies. 
jsx.graphic Deals with vector graphics depending on browsers. 
jsx.http Handles HTTP requests by using XMLHTTPRequest or ActiveX for IE. 
jsx.http.event Event objects and their handlers for HTTP requests. 
jsx.http.rpc Facilitates mechanism for RPC based on HTTP serialization. 
jsx.http.rpc.remote Facilitates client-side for remote object services based on XMLHTTP serialized RPC mechanism. 
jsx.http.rpc.remote.client Basic client-side classes providing remote reflect services to server-side Java classes. 
jsx.http.rpc.server Facilitates server-side for RPC based on HTTP serialization. 
jsx.motion Provides clear-in-mind practicable methodologies for definition and utilization to step-motion models that are useful in designing animation, visual effects and vector graphics. 
jsx.motion.reg Provides regular motion functions and their operations. 
jsx.motion.reg.cmp Provides composite regular motion operations. 
jsx.motion.reg.cmp.bin Provides binary composite regular motion operations. 
jsx.ui Contains general classes for representing user interfaces. 
jsx.ui.box Contains classes representing box widgets. 
jsx.ui.css Contains classes manipulating user interfaces through CSS. 
jsx.ui.ctrl Contains classes representing control widgets. 
jsx.ui.dd Contains classes representing drag-and-drop related widgets. 
jsx.ui.dd.event Drag-and-drop event objects and their handlers. 
jsx.ui.event Event objects and their handlers for the general user interfaces. 
jsx.ui.fx Classes for widgets to add visual effects to their underlying components. 
jsx.ui.fx.event Event objects and their handlers for visual effects. 
jsx.ui.html Classes for HTML elementary widgets. 
jsx.ui.layout Layouts for Container widgets. 
jsx.ui.vect Vector graphic widgets for interactive drawing based on canvas, SVG and VML. 
jsx.ui.vect.canvas For extra vector graphic widgets for interactive drawing based on 2d-canvas. 
jsx.ui.vect.draw For extra vector graphic widgets for interactive drawing based on SVG or VML. 
 

Classes in js used by js
ArrayLike
          An opaque interface resembling JavaScript arrays.
ArrayObject
          An opaque interface resembling JavaScript arrays including the system read-only ones such as HTMLElementCollection, NodeList, Arguments, etc.
Cases
          An opaque interface helping to simulate JavaScript switch statement in the Java language environment.
DateLike
          An opaque interface resembling JavaScript built-in Date objects for manipulating dates and times.
Disposable
          A normal abstract class helping re-compilers in their finalization mechanisms.
Function
          A normal class extended concretely to define a function object, resembling function definition in JavaScript.
Function.Arguments
          An opaque class used inside function definition resembling JavaScript arguments.
Function.Call
          An opaque class used inside function definition resembling JavaScript callee and caller.
Id
          An opaque class to construct an ID which can be used as a field identifier that is globally or locally unique.
Initializer
          An opaque class resembling JavaScript object initializers (also known as object literals).
LiveClass
          An opaque interface representing LiveConnet Java classes of JavaScript.
LiveObject
          An opaque interface representing LiveConnet Java objects of JavaScript.
MathLike
          An opaque interface resembling JavaScript Math object and providing constants and interfaces of useful mathematical functions.
NumberLike
          An opaque interface representing JavaScript numbers.
ObjectLike
          An opaque interface resembling JavaScript objects.
RegExpLike
          An opaque interface resembling JavaScript regular expressions for performing pattern matching on string instances.
Sim
          An abstract internal class for JS Simulation.
StringLike
          An opaque interface resembling JavaScript strings.
Value
          An opaque class resembling JavaScript primitive values.

          An opaque class resembling JavaScript primitive boolean values.

          An opaque class resembling JavaScript primitive byte number values.
Value.Character
          An opaque class resembling JavaScript primitive unsigned short number values.
Value.Double
          An opaque class resembling JavaScript primitive double number values.
Value.Float
          An opaque class resembling JavaScript primitive float number values.
Value.Integer
          An opaque class resembling JavaScript primitive integer number values.
Value.Long
          An opaque class resembling JavaScript primitive long number values.
Value.Member
          An opaque class representing members of its enclosing opaque type.
Value.Number
          An opaque class resembling JavaScript primitive number values.
Value.Numerical
          An opaque class resembling JavaScript primitive number values.
Value.Short
          An opaque class resembling JavaScript primitive short number values.
Value.String
          An opaque class resembling JavaScript primitive string values.
Var
          An opaque class, resembling JavaScript variables, with subclasses being normal by default.
Var.Generic
          An internal class providing the facilities of arbitrary opaque type casting, especially over JavaScript objects in JS Embed Simulation mode, with the help of the opaque wrapping technology.
Var.Member
          An opaque class representing members of its enclosing opaque type.
Var.Mid
          An opaque class representing member IDs.
Vars
          An opaque class resembling JavaScript array literals (also known as array literals) and variable arguments.
